Subject: [PATCH 14/15] dts: gianfar: L2SRAM integration for bd allocation

This provides support for allocation of bd's in L2SRAM.
This option can be enabled via the config variable
CONFIG_GIANFAR_L2SRAM.

Signed-off-by:Yongli He <yongli.he@windriver.com>
Integrated-by: Wei Yang <wei.yang@windriver.com>
---
 arch/powerpc/boot/dts/p2020ds.dts |    6 ++++++
 1 files changed, 6 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/p2020ds.dts b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/p2020ds.dts
index 0ee16b2..726cdb6 100644
--- a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/p2020ds.dts
+++ b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/p2020ds.dts
@@ -19,6 +19,12 @@
 		device_type = "memory";
 	};
 
+	l2sram@fff00000 {
+		device_type = "memory";
+		compatible = "fsl,p2020-l2-cache-controller";
+		reg = <0x0 0xfff00000 0 0x10000>;
+	};
+
 	board_lbc: lbc: localbus@ffe05000 {
 		ranges = <0x0 0x0 0x0 0xe8000000 0x08000000
 			  0x1 0x0 0x0 0xe0000000 0x08000000
